compliance_reasoning: The regulation (409) requires regulated entities to assess and periodically review their conflicts of interest policy at least annually. The document provided is a pension life cover scheme rules document that outlines the rules for company pensions, definitions, scheme benefits, trustee duties, and winding up procedures. It does not appear to be a conflicts of interest policy document, nor does it contain provisions related to conflicts of interest policies or their review. The document is a product documentation for an Executive Pension Life Cover Scheme issued by AIB life, not a regulatory compliance document addressing conflicts of interest.
regulation_text: 409. A regulated entity shall assess and periodically review, on at least an annual basis, its conflicts of interest policy and shall take all appropriate measures to address any deficiencies.
source_name: CENTRAL BANK (SUPERVISION AND ENFORCEMENT) ACT 2013 (SECTION 48) (CONSUMER PROTECTION) REGULATIONS 2025
